Reasoning: The paper discusses non-parametric dimensionality reduction methods, which are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision applications. The focus on regularized loss minimization and singular value truncation suggests a connection to the field of machine learning, specifically in the area of regularization techniques. The mention of new convex regularizers also suggests a connection to optimization and convex programming. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The mention of manifold unfolding and distance maximization suggests a connection to the field of nonlinear dimensionality reduction, which could also place the paper in the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Sound).
